Definition: law) the replacement of one obligation by another by mutual agreement of both parties
Example: usually the replacement of one of the original parties to a contract with the consent of the remaining party
Synonyms: verb, change, novate, replacement, noun, group, law, c, the, of, one, obligation, by, another, mutual, agreement, both, parties, usually, original, to, a, contract, with, consent, remaining, party
Category: noun.act
